nk\": 5.289699553562092e-10, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999961303958407, \"rank\": 3.859972156163518e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999989854923713, \"rank\": 1.0145086801275438e-06, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Self-confessed Olympic nut\", \"from\": 1118, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1150}, {\"ngram\": \"his fifth Games\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1185}, {\"ngram\": \"three bronze medals\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1233}, {\"ngram\": \"Tokyo\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eurosport andDiscovery+TV team\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"his high-profile decision\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"a shock comeback\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1388}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After being persuaded by his eldest son, Robbie, to return, the four-time world champion can not wait to combine the two roles at the first Games on European soil since that storied summer in London 12 years ago.\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1432, \"end\": 1438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"score\": 0.9998178235565803, \"rank\": 0.00015010933579012403, \"text\": \"Robbie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\"}, {\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999961303958407, \"rank\": 3.859972156163518e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his eldest son\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"the four-time world champion\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1479}, {\"ngram\": \"the two roles\", \"from\": 1504, \"to\": 1517}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Games\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1536}, {\"ngram\": \"European soil\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1553}, {\"ngram\": \"that storied summer\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Before I got back to diving, that was my plan - to be involved in the Olympics in some form of journalistic way,\\\" said Daley, speaking at the London Aquatics Centre on Wednesday.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1784, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Aquatics_Centre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London Aquatics Centre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Aquatics_Centre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Aquatics_Centre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"diving\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1633}, {\"ngram\": \"my plan\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1651}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"some form\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1697}, {\"ngram\": \"journalistic way\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1730}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesday\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Then I was like: 'Actually, there is this thing that I want to do and I want to compete.'\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this thing\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were like: 'Why not do both?\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 1910, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Compete, and then come and do this?'\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought: 'That's what I am going to do - I can do my competition and then actually enjoy the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 2054, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my competition\", \"from\": 2002, \"to\": 2016}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2041, \"to\": 2053}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what I'd like to do long-term - I love the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"long-term\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2093}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have never really been a sportsperson and I hate all of that stuff but when it comes to the Olympics, I think there is something really special about that moment.\\\"\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2282, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sportsperson\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2156}, {\"ngram\": \"that stuff\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2185}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2207, \"to\": 2219}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2247}, {\"ngram\": \"that moment\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"US-based Daley, who was Team GB's youngest athlete aged 14 at Beijing 2008,was convinced to launch a remarkable returnwhen his son Robbie, now six, told him he wanted to see him dive at the Games after a visit to the US Olympic & Paralympic Museum in Colorado.\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2308, \"end\": 2315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999970605564173, \"rank\": 2.9383316330693966e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbp